      "message": "As discussed in our chat, we\u0027ll use want/error here because we\u0027re testing a success/error response based on a numerical range, and splitting this into one big test function for all the success cases and another one for the error cases makes it harder to follow and less immediately obvious that the tests are correct.\n\nBut we\u0027re in agreement that as a general rule if statements should be avoided in tests.",
